This paper discusses the evolution of Google Scholar Metrics (GSM) journal rankings and analyses bibliometric indicators. The paper is related to digital libraries (cs.DL) as it discusses the ranking of journals in a digital platform. It also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it analyses bibliometric indicators. The paper also discusses language differences, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). Finally, the paper could be related to cryptography (cs.CY) as it discusses the reliability of the GSM journal rankings.
